<reference id="reference832" xml:lang="en-us">
    <title><ph audience="vmware">APP </ph>Database Configuration Settings</title>
    <refbody>
        <section>
            <p>The <codeph>db.properties</codeph> file located in <codeph>&lt;install_pack_dir>/databases/app_db</codeph> contains the configuration settings for <ph audience="vmware">APP </ph>database access. This configuration is used for the initial setup and schema updates. </p>
        </section>
        <section>
            <title>db.driver.class</title>
            <p>The Java class of the JDBC driver.</p>
            <p>Default: <codeph>org.postgresql.Driver</codeph></p>
        </section>
        <section>
            <title>db.host</title>
            <p>The database host. </p>
            <!--p>Note that in a cluster environment, <codeph>localhost</codeph> must not be used.</p-->
            <p>Default: <codeph>localhost</codeph></p>
        </section>
        <section>
            <title>db.port</title>
            <p>The database port. </p>
            <p>Default: <codeph>5432</codeph></p>
        </section>
        <section>
            <title>db.name</title>
            <p>The name of the database. </p>
            <p>Default: <codeph>bssapp</codeph></p>
        </section>
        <!--section>
            <title>db.timer.name</title>
            <p>The name of the database for timers. </p>
            <p>Default: <codeph>bsstimer</codeph></p>
        </section-->
        <section>
            <title>db.user</title>
            <p>The name of the user to connect to the database. </p>
            <p>Default: <codeph>bssappuser</codeph></p>
        </section>
        <section>
            <title>db.pwd</title>
            <p>The password of the user to connect to the database. </p>
            <p>Default: <codeph>bssappuser</codeph></p>
        </section>
        <section>
            <title>db.type</title>
            <p>The type of the database. </p>
            <p>Default: <codeph>postgresql</codeph></p>
        </section>
    </refbody>
</reference>
